e but the broader principles of fairness and due process in sport.\\\"\", \"from\": 1634, \"to\": 1742, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a matter\", \"from\": 1642, \"to\": 1650}, {\"ngram\": \"the broader principles\", \"from\": 1681, \"to\": 1703}, {\"ngram\": \"fairness\", \"from\": 1707, \"to\": 1715}, {\"ngram\": \"process\", \"from\": 1724, \"to\": 1731}, {\"ngram\": \"sport\", \"from\": 1735, \"to\": 1740}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The IOC has consistently said the boxers from Algeria and Taiwan, who were assigned female at birth and identify as women, complied with all the rules for the Olympic tournament.\", \"from\": 1746, \"to\": 1924, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1750, \"end\": 1753, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.973145684052609e-26, \"text\": \"IOC\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}, {\"begin\": 1792, \"end\": 1799, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"score\": 0.9999897923685536, \"rank\": 9.666406443649946e-06, \"text\": \"Algeria\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Algeria\"}, {\"begin\": 1804, \"end\": 1810, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"score\": 0.999815636846617, \"rank\": 0.00014949206169560583, \"text\": \"Taiwan\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Taiwan\"}, {\"begin\": 1905, \"end\": 1923, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basketball_at_the_1936_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.5897042999226336, \"rank\": 0.691194514988768, \"text\": \"Olympic tournament\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Basketball_at_the_1936_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/re